        "excerpt": "Nail salons depend on repeat clients. Learn how a 5-10% improvement in retention can drive predictable revenue without new leads.",
        "content": "\n\n<h3>The Hidden Cost of Lost Clients</h3>\n<p>Nail salons depend on repeat clients to drive predictable revenue, yet retention is often underestimated. Industry research shows that a relatively small group of returning clients can generate the majority of a salon's income, especially for services that require ongoing maintenance, such as gel fills, acrylics, and pedicures.</p>\n\n<p>When clients fall out of a regular schedule, revenue drops quietly over time.</p>\n\n<h3>How Buildify Proves Value</h3>\n<p>The Buildify ROI Calculator is designed to make this impact visible using simple, real-world inputs. It starts by calculating monthly revenue based on two numbers: average ticket price and total monthly client visits. This establishes a clear baseline that reflects how most nail salons actually operate.</p>\n\n<p>From there, the calculator applies a modest retention improvement of 5–10%. Importantly, this does not assume new customers or increased pricing. It models only the revenue gained by keeping a small percentage of existing visits that would otherwise be lost. The result represents one additional month of retained revenue, not an annual or inflated projection.</p>\n\n<h3>The Cost of Inaction</h3>\n<p>To provide context, the calculator also includes the cost of a traditional custom software build. This is based on common market pricing, which typically includes a significant base cost plus a percentage of monthly revenue. The final figure combines the traditional build cost with just one month of retained revenue, showing how quickly retention gains begin to rival or exceed expensive, one-time solutions.</p>\n\n<p>The insight behind the calculator is straightforward: nail salon growth is not limited by demand, but by consistency. Systems that automate rebooking, reminders, and follow-ups help capture revenue that already exists.</p>",
