        "excerpt": "Salon owners face technical barriers that hinder growth. Learn how Buildify bridges the gap between traditional workflows and digital retention.",
        "content": "\n\n<h3>The Friction Audit</h3>\n<p>Small business owners move in at risk and limited motion when first starting out. Every second matters as time and money are constantly being monitored. Adoption of specific software can save small businesses both time and money, but they come with technical barriers that can cause a business further conflicts.</p>\n\n<h3>Current Operational Challenges</h3>\n<p>Salon owners specifically are constantly being timed with their appointments and satisfaction of customers. A software tool for a hair salon would need to implement legacy booking and POS Systems. Many salons still use outdated methods like texting and calling clients for scheduling, using quick money transfer apps for payments, and taking client notes on physical or online documents.</p>\n<p>Although this is efficient, it can be made better for these systems to track transactions accurately. The problem we face is that software can't personalize the experience to the client. This is especially important for regular clients who have been coming to the salon for years. Another reason is the usage of marketing automation is not implemented enough through salons. Many salons operate based on recommendations by clients.</p>\n\n<h3>The Email & CRM Gap</h3>\n<p>The second barrier for salon owners is the limited email and CRM usage. Client information is taken into account at the time of the appointment, but is not saved as a file to be utilized and better the experience for the next visit. Salons mainly rely on new walk-ins and personal active social media accounts.</p>\n\n<h3>The Buildify Solution</h3>\n<p>A software adoption can change that by running email campaigns and automated text messages for special holidays and discounts. This reminds customers to keep coming back to the salon and reinforces the significance of using software adoption to market to a wider audience. A feature to remind clients of suggested rebookings such as regular trims, color dyes, and eyebrow trims can be suggested to the client once their recommended time frame to come back is near.</p>\n\n<h3>Strategic ROI Strategy</h3>\n<p>The strategic ROI model applies a retention-focused revenue on how the salon's revenue will grow. It does this by calculating the average service price by the monthly clients. The loyalty put in place is to make clients feel like VIP members of an exclusive beauty club. By implementing follow up programs this will likely increase the services produced by 5-10% in repeated visitation rates.</p>\n<p>This is backed by the marketing automations through email and notifications about rebooking. In addition to the exclusive rewards given to royalty members and by monitoring clients through the Centralized client tracking. The mobile accessible design makes it an easy user experience, and with everyone using their phones they are more willing to see text notifications. This will turn the company automation into a successful outcome.</p>\n\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>The strategic outcome for salon owners is to use Buildify as a client retention software as well as a way to track the revenue growth. The acceleration of the software provides customers with security, knowing their services are prioritized.</p>",
